---
// biome-ignore lint/correctness/noUnusedImports: used in Astro template
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Schema Reference"
  description="Complete reference for the clip.yaml schema format — all fields, types, and validation rules."
>
  <div class="docs-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Complete reference for the <code>clip.yaml</code> schema format. This file
      is the single source of truth for your generated CLI.
    </p>

    <h2 id="top-level">Top-Level Fields</h2>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Required</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>name</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Human-readable project name (e.g. <code>"Todo API"</code>)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>alias</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>CLI command name. Must match <code>/^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$/</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>version</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Semver version string (e.g. <code>"1.0.0"</code>)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>baseUrl</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Base URL for all API requests</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>auth</code></td>
            <td><code>AuthConfig</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Authentication configuration</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>endpoints</code></td>
            <td><code>Endpoint[]</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Array of endpoint definitions (minimum 1)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 id="auth">Auth Configuration</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>auth</code> object configures how the generated CLI authenticates
      with your API.
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>type</code></td>
            <td><code>"header"</code></td>
            <td>Auth method. Currently only <code>header</code> is supported.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>headerName</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>HTTP header name (e.g. <code>"X-API-Key"</code>, <code>"Authorization"</code>)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <pre><code>{`auth:
  type: header
  headerName: "X-API-Key"`}</code></pre>

    <h2 id="endpoints">Endpoints</h2>
    <p>
      Each entry in the <code>endpoints</code> array defines one CLI command.
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Required</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>name</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Command name. Must be unique, match <code>/^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$/</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>method</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>HTTP method: <code>GET</code>, <code>POST</code>, <code>PUT</code>, <code>PATCH</code>, <code>DELETE</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>path</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>URL path. Supports <code>:param</code> placeholders</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>description</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Shown in CLI <code>--help</code> output</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>params</code></td>
            <td><code>ParamsConfig</code></td>
            <td>No</td>
            <td>Parameter definitions (path, query, body)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>response</code></td>
            <td><code>ResponseSchema</code></td>
            <td>No</td>
            <td>Expected response shape for test validation</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 id="params">Parameters</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>params</code> object has three optional keys, each mapping
      parameter names to their definitions:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>path</code> — URL path parameters (must match <code>:param</code> placeholders). Become positional CLI arguments.</li>
      <li><code>query</code> — Query string parameters. Become <code>--flag</code> options.</li>
      <li><code>body</code> — JSON body fields. Become <code>--flag</code> options.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>ParamDef</h3>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>type</code></td>
            <td><code>"string" | "number" | "boolean" | "array"</code></td>
            <td>Parameter type (required)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>required</code></td>
            <td><code>boolean</code></td>
            <td>Default <code>false</code>. Required params use <code>requiredOption()</code> in Commander</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>description</code></td>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Shown in CLI help</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>items</code></td>
            <td><code>ParamDef</code></td>
            <td>Required when <code>type: "array"</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>enum</code></td>
            <td><code>(string | number)[]</code></td>
            <td>Restrict to allowed values</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>nullable</code></td>
            <td><code>boolean</code></td>
            <td>Default <code>false</code></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 id="response">Response Schema</h2>
    <p>
      Defines the expected shape of API responses. Used by auto-generated tests
      to validate response structure.
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>type</code></td>
            <td><code>"object" | "array" | "string" | "number" | "boolean"</code></td>
            <td>Response type (required)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>properties</code></td>
            <td><code>Record&lt;string, PropertyDef&gt;</code></td>
            <td>Required when <code>type: "object"</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>items</code></td>
            <td><code>ResponseSchema</code></td>
            <td>Required when <code>type: "array"</code> (recursive)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>
      <strong>PropertyDef</strong> can be a shorthand string (<code>"string"</code>,
      <code>"number"</code>, <code>"boolean"</code>) or a nested <code>ResponseSchema</code>
      for complex types.
    </p>

    <h2 id="validation">Validation Rules</h2>
    <p>
      clip validates your schema beyond structural correctness:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Endpoint names must be <strong>unique</strong></li>
      <li>Every <code>:param</code> in <code>path</code> must have a matching key in <code>params.path</code></li>
      <li>No orphan path params — nothing in <code>params.path</code> that isn't in the URL</li>
      <li>No duplicate <code>method + path</code> combinations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="full-example">Full Example</h2>
    <pre><code>{`name: "Todo API"
alias: todo
version: "1.0.0"
baseUrl: "http://localhost:3000"
auth:
  type: header
  headerName: "X-API-Key"
endpoints:
  - name: list
    method: GET
    path: /todos
    description: "List all todos"
    response:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        properties:
          id: string
          title: string
          completed: boolean

  - name: create
    method: POST
    path: /todos
    description: "Create a new todo"
    params:
      body:
        title:
          type: string
          required: true
    response:
      type: object
      properties:
        id: string
        title: string
        completed: boolean

  - name: get
    method: GET
    path: "/todos/:id"
    description: "Get a todo by ID"
    params:
      path:
        id:
          type: string
          required: true

  - name: update
    method: PATCH
    path: "/todos/:id"
    description: "Update a todo"
    params:
      path:
        id:
          type: string
          required: true
      body:
        title:
          type: string
        completed:
          type: boolean

  - name: delete
    method: DELETE
    path: "/todos/:id"
    description: "Delete a todo"
    params:
      path:
        id:
          type: string
          required: true`}</code></pre>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .docs-prose {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .docs-prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .docs-prose h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .docs-prose h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose pre {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  td {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  td code {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
</style>
